Vice President Kamala Harris visited Crowley's Yacht Yard in Chicago, Illinois to discuss infrastructure investment and job creation. She thanked various leaders and organizations for their contributions and highlighted the importance of investing in America's infrastructure. Harris announced the first round of $12.5 billion in funding to replace and improve bridges across the country, including four bridges in Chicago. She emphasized the economic and environmental benefits of infrastructure investment, such as creating jobs and reducing pollution. Harris concluded by expressing her commitment to building a better future for all Americans.